So are there actually centralized servers on the internet? Like why has 8.8.8.8 and 8.8.4.4 been static for the last few decades? Before I got into computer science I always wondered if there was like some central server somewhere that if bombed would break the whole internet. After listening to your DNS talk it seems there is??

Like I just heard HTTPS has a **public ledger**. Where is this hosted and what happens when it goes down? How long has it been hosted? Has it ever gone down? Has any widespread catastrophes happened due to it?
